                                                                                                                                                                                                     Indians for US baseball team
                      
	New Delhi: Two Indian youngsters chasing the American baseball dream have taken an important first step when the Pittsburgh Pirates signed them up as non-draft free agents.         
	Left-hander Rinku Singh and Dinesh Kumar Patel pitched in front of scouts from the Pirates and other Major League organisations on November 12 before being chosen, a statement on the club website (www.pittsburgh.pirates.mlb.com) said. (Reuters)                                                                                                                          
